  "@type": "sc:Dataset",
  "name": "Comparative Toxicogenomics Database",
  "conformsTo": "http://mlcommons.org/croissant/1.0",
  "description": "The Comparative Toxicogenomics Database (CTD) is a robust, publicly available database designed to advance the understanding of how environmental chemicals impact human health. It provides manually curated information on chemical–gene/protein interactions, chemical–disease, and gene–disease relationships. This data is integrated with functional and pathway information to help generate hypotheses about the molecular mechanisms underlying environmentally influenced diseases. CTD also includes ongoing projects for manual curation of exposome data and chemical–phenotype relationships to identify pre-disease biomarkers resulting from environmental exposures.",
  "citeAs": "Davis AP, Wiegers TC, Sciaky D, Barkalow F, Strong M, Wyatt B, Wiegers J, McMorran R, Abrar S, Mattingly CJ Comparative Toxicogenomics Database’s 20th anniversary: update 2025. Nucleic Acids Res. 2024 Oct 10.",
  "license": "The CTD data and software are provided for research and educational purposes only. Commercial use is prohibited without prior express written permission from MDI Biological Laboratory and NC State University. It is provided 'as is' without warranties. Use in publications or applications requires citation, hyperlinking to applicable CTD data pages, and notification to CTD regarding the use. NLM-derived data is subject to additional NLM terms.",
